            <h3 style="color:blue;"><b>Success Story of Shriniwas Bagal ,
              Organic Farmer</b>
              

            </h3>
             
               
 <p>
       
        <a>Background - </a></p>
         
             <p> <br />   Born in 1959  in a small village Chikurde , Mr. Shriniwas  Bagal completed his education in Pharmacy in 1981. 
     In year 1989 he started conventional farming in village Chikurde. After 10 years of  Successful chemical farming ,he experienced limitations in conventional farming. It was difficult to solve various problems in chemical farming such as paste management , fungal and viral infections on crops . This made Mr. Shriniwas to start the Organic Farming.<br /><br />

 Chemical farming-<br /><br />

    After so many problems in chemical farming , he decided to practice organic methods in his 16 acres of land in Chikurde. For getting success in  Organic Farming,he visited various Organic Farms in Sutgatti , Bedkihal , Ajara , etc . He started the use of Amrutpani – an Organic culture , made from cow dung , ghee and honey . Also he used cow urine (gomutra) and neem leaves , for paste control .<br />

 Change to Organic Farming -
 <br />

    In 1999 he succeded to get satisfactory results for organic cultivation of crops like Groundnuts ,Sugarcane ,Wheat ,Mustard , Rice and  other intercrops like onion , garlic ,gramme , vegetables such as cabbage , cauliflower , tomato , guar , methi , coriander etc    Farm Yard Mannure was produced in his own farm bearing more than 16 cattles , consisting of Indian Cow , Buffalowes . This helped to reduce cost of production in farming . Also the quality of agriculture products was different and remarkable . . <br />
    Step – Organizational Group -<br />

     By this time , Mr. Shriniwas started selling these organic products , in market . He formed an organic co – operative organization VASUNDHARA SHASHWAT SHETI SAMVARDHAN SANSHTHA Limited in 2006 , a registered farmers group . 67 organic farmers from Kolhapur , Sangli , Satara and Solapur districts came together to market their organic prodcuts at urban cities like Mumbai ,Pune ,Bengaluru ,Panjim etc .
    Mr. Shriniwas is working as founder Vice – President of VASUNDHARA SHASHWAT SHETI SAMVARDHAN SANSHTHA Limited . He is leading this organization since 2006 .<br />
     <br />PGS Certification -<br />

    In year 2008 , 54 farmers from VASUNDHARA , got organic certification under PGS India Organic Council . All organic farmers are selling their agriproducts under banner VASUNDHARA .<br />
     <br />Achievements -<br />

     As a result of this hardwork for education and promotion of  organic farmers , The Maharashtra State Government honoured Mr. Shriniwas Bagal , as Krishibhushan , Organic Farming in 2012. <br />




